{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, for any f, f ∈ C(R d, R D) we have Λ(f) -Λ( f) ∞ = sup (x,y)∈R d ×R D ℓ f (x), y -ℓ f (x), y ≤ L ℓ ∥f -f ∥ ∞.",
    "Consequentially, Λ is L ℓ -Lipschitz.Lemma 8 (Covering Number Bounds: Random LoRA Class).",
    "Consider the setting of Lemma 4.",
    "For each random initialization ω ∈ Ω on the non-trainable parameters (B (t)) T +1 t=1, define the LoRA function space F equipped with the metric induced by the uniform norm ∥ • ∥ ∞:F def.",
    "= F(ω, M) = {LoRA(ω, (A (t)) T +1 t=1) ∈ C([0, 1] d, R D): |A (t) ij | ≤ M, ∀t, i, j}."
  ]
}